radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is entirely fluid filled and dilated up to 1 cm, with increased soft tissue thickening at the base of the cecum. A tortuous somewhat tubular irregular hypodensity may represent a dilated, fluid-filled tortuous proximal appendix or periappendiceal fluid collection/abscess, measuring approximately 2.2 x 1.4 cm. Minimal dependent atelectasis noted, but no pleural effusion. Liver enhances homogeneously without concerning lesions. Mild diffuse periportal edema present. No biliary dilatation or concerning lesions in kidneys, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, or adrenal glands. The remainder of the colon is unremarkable. A 2.5-cm right adnexal cyst noted, with a small amount of simple free fluid in the cul-de-sac. Degenerative changes in the spine most severe at the L5-S1 level.
